sysDateAndTime.name: sysDateAndTime
sysDateAndTime.description: The date and time of this device can be set.DateAndTime is in octet mode which does not include time-zone information.

sysIPAddr.name: sysIPAddr
sysIPAddr.description: The device lacks of IP address

slotBoardTable.name: slotBoardTable
slotBoardTable.description: The board information table describes the information of the type, the status and the software version etc. of the boards in various slot of the EXPERT.

slotBoardEntry.name: slotBoardEntry
slotBoardEntry.description: The object defined by this line describes the information of the board in the slot.

slotBoardSlotNo.name: slotBoardSlotNo
slotBoardSlotNo.description: Slot number, it forms the index for this table. The EXPERT includes 16 slots. The value range of which is from 0 to 15.

slotBoardType.name: slotBoardType
slotBoardType.description: The type of slot board, it describes the type of board to be inserted in the slot among which null (100) indicates null slot. When the variable value is null (100), the variable values of subsequent rows of this row has no meaning, all of which are 0 or null.

slotBoardNo.name: slotBoardNo
slotBoardNo.description: Board number, ranging from 0 to 11. When the slot is null, the returned value is 65535 indicating invalidation.

slotBoardStatus.name: slotBoardStatus
slotBoardStatus.description: Board status not-install(0) Not-installed normal(1) Normal fault(2) Fault active-normal(3) The active one is normal active-error(4) The active one is faulty back-normal(5) The backup one is normal back-error(6) The backup one is faulty When the board type is null (100), the board status returns not-install (0) to indicate invalidation.

slotBoardPCBVersion.name: slotBoardPCBVersion
slotBoardPCBVersion.description: Description of Board PCB version. When the board type is null (100), the returned value is \0 indicating invalidation.

slotBoardBIOSVersion.name: slotBoardBIOSVersion
slotBoardBIOSVersion.description: Description of Board BIOS version, when the board type is null (100), the returned value is \0 indicating invalidation.

slotBoardSoftwareVersion.name: slotBoardSoftwareVersion
slotBoardSoftwareVersion.description: Board system version number. When the board type is null (100), the returned value is \0 indicating invalidation.

slotBoardLogicVersion.name: slotBoardLogicVersion
slotBoardLogicVersion.description: Description of Board logic version. When the board type is null (100), the returned value is \0 indicating invalidation.

slotBoardDSPVersion.name: slotBoardDSPVersion
slotBoardDSPVersion.description: Description of Board DSP version. When the board type is null (100), the returned value is \0 indicating invalidation.

slotBoardOtherVersion.name: slotBoardOtherVersion
slotBoardOtherVersion.description: Description of other versions. When the board type is null (100), the returned value is \0 indicating invalidation.

slotBoardCPURatio.name: slotBoardCPURatio
slotBoardCPURatio.description: Board CPU seizure ratio. When the board type is null (100), the returned value is \0 indicating invalidation.

slotBoardCPUStatus.name: slotBoardCPUStatus
slotBoardCPUStatus.description: Board CPU status normal(1) indicating CPU is normal overload1(2) indicating CPU is in the status of level 1 overload overload2(3) indicating CPU is in the status of level 2 overload overload3(4) indicating CPU is in the status of level 3 overload overload4(5) indicating CPU is in the status of level 4 overload When the board type is null (100), the returned value is no-meaning (0) indicating invalidation.

slotBoardMemorySize.name: slotBoardMemorySize
slotBoardMemorySize.description: Board memory size, including used part and unused part. When the board type is null (100), the returned value is \0 indicating invalidation.

slotBoardUsableMemory.name: slotBoardUsableMemory
slotBoardUsableMemory.description: Board usable memory size. It means the unused memory of the board. When the board type is null (100), the returned value is \0 indicating invalidation.

boardResetInfoTable.name: boardResetInfoTable
boardResetInfoTable.description: Board reset information table. It describes the causes and time of the previous reset of the EXPERT board.

boardResetInfoEntry.name: boardResetInfoEntry
boardResetInfoEntry.description: The object defined by this line describes the causes and time of the previous reset of the board.

boardResetInfoSlotNo.name: boardResetInfoSlotNo
boardResetInfoSlotNo.description: Slot number. This object forms the index for this table. EXPERT includes 16 slots with the value range from 0 to 15.

boardResetInfoReason.name: boardResetInfoReason
boardResetInfoReason.description: Board reset causes. The meaning of various enumeration values are as follows: slot-err(0), he input slot number is wrong. slot-nouse(1), The slot has not been configured with board. no-reset-record(2), This board has no reset record. lost-connect(3), The active SMB lost connection with this board. user-cmd(4), User delivers reset command. smb-snd-msg(5), SMD delivers reset message. abnormal(6), Reset is caused by abnormal error board-fault(7), It is unable to query due to board fault failed(8), Query failure /*SMB reset cause 20 ~ 49 */ swap-smb(20), Switching SMB board mt-reboot(21), User delivers the command of reset board all. /* VSP reset cause 50 ~ 79 */ /* HRB reset cause 80 ~ 109 */ /* MSTU reset cause 80 ~ 109 */ cfg-failed(110), Configuration failure failed-531(111), 531 failure failed-528(112), 528 failure failed-525(113) 525 failure

boardResetInfoTime.name: boardResetInfoTime
boardResetInfoTime.description: The time of previous board reset. If the board has not reset before, the returned date and time are not defined.

e1InfoTable.name: e1InfoTable
e1InfoTable.description: E1 information table. It describes the information of various E1 port on the VSP board and MSTU board.

e1InfoEntry.name: e1InfoEntry
e1InfoEntry.description: The object defined by this line describes the information of the E1 port.

e1InfoSlotNo.name: e1InfoSlotNo
e1InfoSlotNo.description: Slot number. This object and e1InfoE1NoInBoard form the index for this table which is used as the only one flag indicating a E1 in certain board. The value range of slot number is from 0 to 15.

e1InfoE1NoInBoard.name: e1InfoE1NoInBoard
e1InfoE1NoInBoard.description: The E1 number inside the board. This object and e1InfoSlotNo form the index for this table with the value range from 0 to 62. Actually, the VSP board contains four E1 ports but additional space for 12 ports is reserved. Thus for the VSP board, the value range of this object is from 0 to 15. The MSTU board contains 63 E1 ports. Thus for the MSTU board, the value range of this object is from 0 to 62.

e1InfoE1No.name: e1InfoE1No
e1InfoE1No.description: The global E1 number in the EXPERT. When the device include 2 MSTU boards and 10 VSP boards, the number of E1s is the most which is up to 286; thus the value range of this object is from 0 to 285.

e1InfoE1Type.name: e1InfoE1Type
e1InfoE1Type.description: E1 type, the meaning of various enumeration valuesis as follows: no1(0) China No. 1 or R2 tup(1) SS7 TUP isup(2) SS7 ISUP pra(3) ISDN DSS1

e1InfoE1Status.name: e1InfoE1Status
e1InfoE1Status.description: The status of E1 port, the meaning of various enumeration values is as follows: uninstall(0) Not-installed fault(1) Fault normal(2) Normal alarm(3) Alarm

e1InfoE1LoopBackStatus.name: e1InfoE1LoopBackStatus
e1InfoE1LoopBackStatus.description: The loop status of E1 port, the meaning of various enumeration valuesis as follows: remote-loop(2), in the status of remote loop local-loop(4), in the status of local loop rmt-lcl-loop(6), in remote and local loop status simultaneously payload-loop(8), in the status of payload loop rmt-payload-loop(10), in remote and payload loop status simultaneously lcl-payload-loop(12), in local and payload loop status simultaneously rmt-lcl-payload-loop(14), in local, remote and payload loop status simultaneously no-loop(16) not in loop status There are three types of loop: local loop, remote loop and payload loop which are not exclusive to one another, and can exist simultaneously.

e1InfoE1PCMPara.name: e1InfoE1PCMPara
e1InfoE1PCMPara.description: PCM alarm parameter. This value is an 8-digit integer and each digit indicates one type of alarm as below: D7 D6 D5 D4 D3 D2 D1 D0 | | | | | | | |__ meaningless, fixed to 1 | | | | | | | | | | | | | |__Remote multiframe alarm, RMF | | | | | | | | | | | |__ TS16 all 1 | | | | | | | | | |__Slide code | | | | | | | |__Disconnection | | | | | |__Remote frame alarm, RFA | | | |___ Multiframe out-of-sync, MFA | |___Frame out-of-sync, FAS Note: Dx = 0 Alarm 1 = normal

mfcInfoTable.name: mfcInfoTable
mfcInfoTable.description: MFC information table. It describes the status information of the MFC chip on the VSP boards.

mfcInfoEntry.name: mfcInfoEntry
mfcInfoEntry.description: The object defined by this line describes the status information of the MFC chip.

mfcInfoMfcNo.name: mfcInfoMfcNo
mfcInfoMfcNo.description: Global MFC number. This variable value equals to the logic board number of the MFC-located VSP board with the range from 0 to 11.

mfcInfoMfcStatus.name: mfcInfoMfcStatus
mfcInfoMfcStatus.description: The status of the MFC chip, the meaning of various enumeration values is as follows: normal(0), The MFC is in normal status. error(1), MFC fault num-err(2), The input MFC number is wrong. num-nouse(3) The MFC with this number is not configured.

seekUserEntry.name: seekUserEntry
seekUserEntry.description: This table contains operation objects for nas board user query.

seekUserType.name: seekUserType
seekUserType.description: User query operation types: ByIP(0): Query on the basis of IP addresses. ByUserName(1): Query on the basis of user names. ByCallingNumber(2): Query on the basis of calling numbers.

seekUserRst.name: seekUserRst
seekUserRst.description: Query results: success(0):The query succeeds. fail(1): The query fails. end(2): The query ends.

kickUserRst.name: kickUserRst

vspPortStatusTable.name: vspPortStatusTable
vspPortStatusTable.description: Port status table of VSP board and HSP board. It indicates the statuses of DSP ports and ISDN ports of VSP board or HSP board.

vspPortStatusEntry.name: vspPortStatusEntry
vspPortStatusEntry.description: It contains objects describing statuses of DSP ports and ISDN ports of VSP board or HSP board.

vspPortStatusSlotNo.name: vspPortStatusSlotNo
vspPortStatusSlotNo.description: Slot number of VSP board or HSP board, forming the index of this table. The value range is 0-15.

vspPortStatusISDNPortStatus.name: vspPortStatusISDNPortStatus
vspPortStatusISDNPortStatus.description: ISDN port statuses. There are 62 bytes totally. Every byte indicates the statuses of two ports. That is, every 4 bits indicate status of one port. This object can totally indicate statuses of 124 ISDN ports. The following is the corresponding relations between port statuses and 4-bit values indicating corresponding port status. 0 NOINSTALL Uninstalled 1 IDLE Idle 2 BUSY Busy 3 FAULT Fault 4 TESTING Test 5 BLOCK Blocked 6 OTHER Other 15 NO-MEANING No meaning If VSP contains less than 124 ports, those exceeding the number of ISDN ports of this board are indicated with 15 NO-MEANING. For HSP board, this object has its meaning. For VSP board, only DSP ports are provided and NOINSTALL is used for all ports of this object.

vspPortStatusDSPPortStatus.name: vspPortStatusDSPPortStatus
vspPortStatusDSPPortStatus.description: DSP port statuses. There are 60 bytes totally. Every byte indicates statuses of two ports. That is, every 4 bits indicate status of one port. This object can totally indicate statuses of 120 DSP ports. The following is the corresponding relations between port statuses and 4-bit values indicating corresponding port status. 0 NOINSTALL Uninstalled 1 IDLE Idle 2 BUSY Busy 3 FAULT Fault 4 TESTING Test 5 BLOCK Blocked 6 OTHER Other 15 NO-MEANING No meaning If VSP contains less than 120 ports, those exceeding the number of DSP ports of this board are indicated with 15 NO-MEANING. For VSP board, this object has its meaning. For HSP board, only ISDN ports are provided and NOINSTALL is used for all ports of this object.

vspPortStatisticsTable.name: vspPortStatisticsTable
vspPortStatisticsTable.description: Port statistics table of VSP board and HSP board. It contains the numbers of DSP ports and IDSN ports in various statuses of VSP board or HSP board.

vspPortStatisticsEntry.name: vspPortStatisticsEntry
vspPortStatisticsEntry.description: It contains objects describing numbers of DSP ports and IDSN ports in various statuses of VSP board or HSP board.

vspPortStatisticsSlotNo.name: vspPortStatisticsSlotNo
vspPortStatisticsSlotNo.description: Slot number of VSP board or HSP board. It forms the index of this table.

vspPortStatisticsISDNTotalPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsISDNTotalPorts
vspPortStatisticsISDNTotalPorts.description: Number of total ISDN ports of this HSP board. For VSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsISDNNoInstallPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsISDNNoInstallPorts
vspPortStatisticsISDNNoInstallPorts.description: Number of uninstalled ISDN ports of this HSP board. For VSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsISDNIdelPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsISDNIdelPorts
vspPortStatisticsISDNIdelPorts.description: Number of idle ISDN ports of this HSP board. For VSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsISDNBusyPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsISDNBusyPorts
vspPortStatisticsISDNBusyPorts.description: Number of busy ISDN ports of this HSP board. For VSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsISDNFaultPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsISDNFaultPorts
vspPortStatisticsISDNFaultPorts.description: Number of fault ISDN ports of this HSP board. For VSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsISDNTestPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsISDNTestPorts
vspPortStatisticsISDNTestPorts.description: Number of test ISDN ports of this HSP board. For VSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsISDNBlockPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsISDNBlockPorts
vspPortStatisticsISDNBlockPorts.description: Number of blocked ISDN ports of this HSP board. For VSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsISDNOtherPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsISDNOtherPorts
vspPortStatisticsISDNOtherPorts.description: Number of ISDN ports in other statuses of this HSP board. For VSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsDSPTotalPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsDSPTotalPorts
vspPortStatisticsDSPTotalPorts.description: Number of total DSP ports of this VSP board. For HSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsDSPNoInstallPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsDSPNoInstallPorts
vspPortStatisticsDSPNoInstallPorts.description: Number of uninstalled DSP ports of this VSP board. For HSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsDSPIdelPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsDSPIdelPorts
vspPortStatisticsDSPIdelPorts.description: Number of idle DSP ports of this VSP board. For HSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsDSPBusyPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsDSPBusyPorts
vspPortStatisticsDSPBusyPorts.description: Number of busy DSP ports of this VSP board. For HSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsDSPFaultPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsDSPFaultPorts
vspPortStatisticsDSPFaultPorts.description: Number of fault DSP ports of this VSP board. For HSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsDSPTestPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsDSPTestPorts
vspPortStatisticsDSPTestPorts.description: Number of test DSP ports of this VSP board. For HSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsDSPBlockPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsDSPBlockPorts
vspPortStatisticsDSPBlockPorts.description: Number of blocked DSP ports of this VSP board. For HSP board, this object is 0.

vspPortStatisticsDSPOtherPorts.name: vspPortStatisticsDSPOtherPorts
vspPortStatisticsDSPOtherPorts.description: Number of DSP ports in other statuses of this VSP board. For HSP board, this object is 0.

vspNASCallTable.name: vspNASCallTable
vspNASCallTable.description: Access service call status table of VSP board and HSP board. It describes the information of various statuses of calls through ports of VSP board and HSP board.

vspNASCallEntry.name: vspNASCallEntry
vspNASCallEntry.description: It contains objects describing call status information of VSP board and HSP board.

vspNASCallSlotNo.name: vspNASCallSlotNo
vspNASCallSlotNo.description: Slot number of VSP board or HSP board. It forms the index of this table.

vspNASCallPortNo.name: vspNASCallPortNo
vspNASCallPortNo.description: Port number of VSP board or HSP board. For VSP board, it is DSP port number and the range is 0-199. For HSP board, it is ISDN port and the range is 0-123.

vspNASCallPortType.name: vspNASCallPortType
vspNASCallPortType.description: Port type. It indicates the port is an MODEM port or an ISDN port. MODEM port is DSP port that we usually say.

vspNASCallValidFlag.name: vspNASCallValidFlag
vspNASCallValidFlag.description: Call validity flag. It indicates whether there is any call through this port currently. invalid(1) indicates that there is no call through the port currently and the data has no meaning. valid(2) indicates that there is a call through this port.

vspNASCallStartingTime.name: vspNASCallStartingTime
vspNASCallStartingTime.description: Start time of this call. If vspNASCallValidFlag is invalid, this object returns 0000 year 0 moth 0 date 0 hour 0 minute 0 second.

vspNASCallCallingNumber.name: vspNASCallCallingNumber
vspNASCallCallingNumber.description: Calling number of this call. If vspNASCallValidFlag is invalid, this object will return NULL.

vspNASCallCalledNumber.name: vspNASCallCalledNumber
vspNASCallCalledNumber.description: Called number of this call. If vspNASCallValidFlag is invalid, this object will return NULL.

vspNASCallDataRate.name: vspNASCallDataRate
vspNASCallDataRate.description: Receiving speed rate. The receive rate for ISDN calls or the baud rate for modem calls. A value of 0 is returned if entry is invalid.

vspNASCallXmitRate.name: vspNASCallXmitRate
vspNASCallXmitRate.description: Sending speed rate. The transmit rate for ISDN calls or the baud rate for modem calls. A value of 0 is returned if entry is invalid.

vspNASCallDirection.name: vspNASCallDirection
vspNASCallDirection.description: Call direction. A value of no-meaning(3) is returned if entry is invalid

vspNASSessionTable.name: vspNASSessionTable
vspNASSessionTable.description: Access service session information table of VSP board and HSP board. It describes the information of various statuses of connection users through ports of VSP board.

vspNASSessionEntry.name: vspNASSessionEntry
vspNASSessionEntry.description: It contains objects describing connection user information of VSP board and HSP board.

vspNASSessionSlotNo.name: vspNASSessionSlotNo
